<paragraph id="8BCD36821912415649DA06AAFE4C17D4" blockId="0.[926,1383,1391,1447]" box="[926,1383,1423,1447]" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">
<typeStatus id="54C988201912415649DA06AAF8F817D4" box="[926,979,1423,1447]" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">Type</typeStatus>
species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D01191241564E7206B5FE4C17D4" authority="Schmitz, 1927" authorityName="Schmitz" authorityYear="1927" box="[1078,1383,1423,1447]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Abaristophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arctophila">
<emphasis id="B906EA90191241564E7206B5FFE817D4" box="[1078,1219,1424,1447]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">A. arctophila</emphasis>
Schmitz, 1927
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD368219124156490706E8FEA11549" blockId="0.[835,1474,1485,1850]" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">
The treatment of 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D01191241564E6406EBFEA01796" authority="Schmitz, 1927" authorityName="Schmitz" authorityYear="1927" box="[1056,1419,1485,1509]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Abaristophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B906EA90191241564E6406EBFFE51796" box="[1056,1230,1486,1509]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">Abaristophora</emphasis>
Schmitz, 1927
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D0119124156490706C8FFA21477" authority="Schmitz, 1939" authorityName="Schmitz" authorityYear="1939" box="[835,1161,1516,1540]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Abaristophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Antipodiphora">
<emphasis id="B906EA9019124156490706C8F8CB1477" box="[835,992,1517,1540]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">Antipodiphora</emphasis>
Schmitz, 1939
</taxonomicName>
as distinct genera was long disputed (Schmitz, 1939; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B73191241564E26052EFE361450" author="Borgmeier, T" box="[1122,1309,1547,1571]" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" pagination="1 - 256" refId="ref2580" refString="Borgmeier, T., 1963. Revision of the North American phorid flies. Part 1. The Phorinae, Aenigmatiinae and Metopininae, except Megaselia (Diptera, Phoridae). Studia Entomologia, 6: 1 - 256." type="journal article" year="1963">Borgmeier, 1963</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B73191241564F6F052EFE961450" author="Brown, B" box="[1323,1469,1547,1571]" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" pagination="307 - 322" refId="ref2622" refString="Brown, B. V., 1988. Additions to the phorid chapter in the Manual of Nearctic Diptera, Volume 2 (Diptera: Phoridae). Canadian Entomologist, 120: 307 - 322." type="journal article" year="1988">Brown, 1988</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B73191241564907050FF8511431" author="Brown, B" box="[835,890,1578,1602]" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" pagination="1 - 144" refId="ref2660" refString="Brown, B. V., 1992. Generic revision of Phoridae of the Nearctic Region and phylogenetic classification of Phoridae, Sciadoceridae and Ironomyiidae (Diptera: Phoridea). Memoirs of the Entomological Society of Canada, 164: 1 - 144." type="journal article" year="1992">1992</bibRefCitation>
) until Disney &amp; Ross (1997) treated 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D01191241564F4D050EFE8E1431" authorityName="Schmitz" authorityYear="1939" box="[1289,1445,1579,1602]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Abaristophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Antipodiphora">
<emphasis id="B906EA90191241564F4D050EFE8E1431" box="[1289,1445,1579,1602]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">Antipodiphora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a subgenus of 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D011912415649A2056FFFA91412" authorityName="Schmitz" authorityYear="1927" box="[998,1154,1610,1633]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Abaristophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B906EA901912415649A2056FFFA91412" box="[998,1154,1610,1633]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">Abaristophora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Nakayama &amp; Shima (2006) gave detailed information on the status of each genus and the relation to its closest relative genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D01191241564EB705ADFE4114EC" box="[1267,1386,1672,1695]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Borophaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B906EA90191241564EB705ADFE4114EC" box="[1267,1386,1672,1695]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">Borophaga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Before this article, 12 species were known worldwide (Table 1.). The species of subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D01191241564E1405E0FFC714AF" authorityName="Schmitz" authorityYear="1927" box="[1104,1260,1733,1756]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Abaristophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B906EA90191241564E1405E0FFC714AF" box="[1104,1260,1733,1756]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">Abaristophora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are restricted to the northern hemisphere except the undescribed species in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B73191241564F3E05C1F8A11569" author="Brown, B" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" pagination="1 - 144" refId="ref2660" refString="Brown, B. V., 1992. Generic revision of Phoridae of the Nearctic Region and phylogenetic classification of Phoridae, Sciadoceridae and Ironomyiidae (Diptera: Phoridea). Memoirs of the Entomological Society of Canada, 164: 1 - 144." type="journal article" year="1992">Brown (1992)</bibRefCitation>
from 
<collectingCountry id="F36576121912415649950427FF6A1569" box="[977,1089,1794,1818]" name="Venezuela" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
, while the species of the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D011912415649070406F8F41549" authorityName="Schmitz" authorityYear="1939" box="[835,991,1827,1850]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Abaristophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Antipodiphora">
<emphasis id="B906EA901912415649070406F8F41549" box="[835,991,1827,1850]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">Antipodiphora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
seems to have an Oriental distribution.
</paragraph>
